1428
01:49:08,929 --> 01:49:15,450
[SPEAKER_12]: It's a facilitated discussion of small groups of people, often with some type of shared identity or identity.

1429
01:49:15,530 --> 01:49:22,852
[SPEAKER_12]: So it could be people who ran and didn't get elected or older adults or youth or immigrants.

1430
01:49:23,792 --> 01:49:25,933
[SPEAKER_12]: It's conducted by trained facilitators,

1431
01:49:27,166 --> 01:49:32,370
[SPEAKER_12]: It's structured, so we would create a list of questions that we would direct to the focus group.

1432
01:49:33,171 --> 01:49:50,526
[SPEAKER_12]: The reason you do focus groups as opposed to surveys is that you're going to get more open-ended, broad, and qualitative answers, meaning answers you can't count, but that give you kind of nuanced information, more complex responses.

1433
01:49:51,423 --> 01:49:57,530
[SPEAKER_12]: It's a good way to gather in-depth information about a community's thoughts or opinions on a topic.

1434
01:49:58,992 --> 01:50:02,436
[SPEAKER_12]: It's best to do questions that you can't answer, like on the survey.

1435
01:50:02,616 --> 01:50:09,765
[SPEAKER_12]: So it's good to think through what aren't we answering or what's a little more nuanced that we're not asking on our survey.

1436
01:50:12,340 --> 01:50:30,749
[SPEAKER_12]: What makes a good focus group is the leaders of the focus group really need to make an effort that all participants feel like it's a safe space to share their opinions without fear of feeling rejected, retaliated, or that there'll be some kind of negative consequences.

1437
01:50:30,769 --> 01:50:36,832
[SPEAKER_12]: So you're really creating this safe space where anyone can kind of share their ideas or opinions.

1438
01:50:37,670 --> 01:50:41,271
[SPEAKER_12]: It's the role of the facilitator to not counter that.

1439
01:50:41,451 --> 01:50:48,834
[SPEAKER_12]: We just want people to be able to share what they're thinking and tell us their answers without feeling like we're judging anything they say.

1440
01:50:48,934 --> 01:50:51,555
[SPEAKER_12]: So there's no right answer as long as it's a safe space.

1441
01:50:52,576 --> 01:51:01,619
